                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "This mod is given at the penultimate mission of The Sacrifice , automatically ranked to level 5. Additional unranked mods can be bought from Cephalon Simaris for 100,000 Standing 100,000 ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Umbral Intensify is essentially the Intensify mod with Legendary rarity and 5 more ranks. It is considered the same mod as its Rare counterpart, and thus both mods cannot be equipped together."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The set bonus for Umbral Intensify increases the Ability Strength given by the mod by 25% of mod's value when using 2 set pieces and 75% when using 3. At max rank with full set bonus, Umbral Intensify grants an Ability Strength increase of 77% , and increases Tau resistance by 19.25% ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Resistance values in the above stat table are calculated based on set bonus values, displayed values are rounded to the first decimal place ingame."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Unlike Umbral Intensify , Umbral Fiber and Umbral Vitality increase their stats by 30% and 80% due to set bonuses instead of 25% and 75%."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "This mod outperforms Intensify from rank 7 alone, from rank 6 with 2 set pieces and from rank 4 with 3 set pieces."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Umbral Intensify",
                  "pageId": 1312621,
                  "revisionId": 2792489,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Umbra mods have a unique polarity, whose matching polarity can currently only be found on Excalibur Umbra , Exalted Umbra Blade , and the Skiajati . It is possible to (re-)add a polarity to a mod slot but only through the use of Umbra Forma , which can be obtained either directly, from Nightwave , or built with blueprints purchasable once every 8 weeks with Steel Essence . Given the extremely limited rate of acquisition, it is advised not to re-Forma any mod slot with an polarity."
                }
